<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-09-10T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-09-10T16:00:00-05:00" n="687" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d687">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">823.30/111: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-10T16:00:00-05:00">September 10, 1930—4
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:44 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>199. Admiral Pye informs me that the junta desire to retain the services
                            of himself as well as Spears, Gunnell, and Compton. Davy’s contract,
                            which was shortly to expire, terminated by mutual agreement. He has been
                            treated generously by the junta. Wyatt’s contract will be canceled with
                            3 months’ pay.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dearing</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>